    - m_Type: 0
      Title:
        m_Untranslated: 
      Text:
        m_Untranslated: 'This is pretty similar in structure to the direct Gizmos
          code, except here we needed to specify what plane to draw the disc on (try
          changing it from <c>Vector3.back</c> to <c>Vector3.left</c> or <c>Vector3.up</c>
          to see what happens and why we chose <c>Vector3.back</c>).

          Note
          the use of <c>#if UNITY_EDITOR</c> here -- this fancy code is a pre-processor
          directive, to tell Unity to ignore this code if making an EXE or WebGL
          build.

          Have a look at the other gizmos and handles you can use:

          <a>https://docs.unity3d.com/ScriptReference/Gizmos.html</a>

          <a>https://docs.unity3d.com/ScriptReference/Handles.html</a>

          <a>https://docs.unity3d.com/ScriptReference/Debug.DrawLine.html</a>'
